432\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0432\u0438\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044c (\u0422\u044e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u044c)-2.jpg|[[Tyumen]]\nFile:\u041a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043d\u043e\u044f\u0440\u0441\u043a (\u043d\u043e\u0447\u043d\u043e\u0439).jpg|[[Krasnoyarsk]]\nFile:\u0425\u0430\u0431\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a, \u0441\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440.jpg|[[Transfiguration Cathedral, Khabarovsk|Transfiguration Cathedral]], [[Khabarovsk]]\nFile:Sakha beauty.jpg|[[Yakut people|Yakut]] woman in traditional dress, [[Sakha Republic]]\nFile:Ivolga.jpg|[[Ivolginsky Datsan]] - [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] temple in [[Buryatia]]\nFile:Jezioro Bajka\u0142 2.jpg|[[Lake Baikal]]\nFile:\u0423\u0442\u0440\u043e \u044f\u0441\u043d\u043e\u0435.jpg|[[Altai Mountains]]\nFile:Tundra in Siberia.jpg|[[Tundra]] in [[Siberia]]\nFile:Kronotsky volcano.jpg|[[Kronotsky|Kronotsky volcano]] in the [[Kamchatka peninsula]]\nFile:\u0428\u0430\u043c\u0430\u043d \u0422\u0430\u0448\u043e\u043e\u043b \u0411\u0443\u0443\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041a\u0443\u043d\u0433\u0430 - \u043e\u0431\u0440\u044f\u0434 \u043e\u0441\u0432\u044f\u0449\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430 (\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0433).jpg|[[Buryat people|Buryat]] [[Shamanism|shaman]] consecrating an [[ovoo]]\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Russia}}\n<!-- {{Wikipedia-Books}} -->\n{{commons}}\n<!-- {{main|Outline of North Asia|Index of North Asia-related articles}} -->\n<!-- *[[Bibliography of North Asia]] -->\n*[[Arctic|Arctic Region]]\n*[[Far North (Russia)|Far North]]\n*[[Siberia]]\n*[[European Russia]]\n*[[Asia]]\n*[[Geography of Asia]]\n*[[Northeast Asia]]\n*[[Russian Far East]]\n*[[Ural (region)|Ural region]]\n*[[Siberian High]], a semipermament anticyclone\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Regions of Asia}}\n{{Countries of Asia}}\n{{Asia topics}}\n{{Russia topics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:North Asia| ]]\n[[Category:Regions of the Arctic]]\n", 